{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"cxrxitu3f0mwbkymb3t367n","title":"Tennis Defeated (Induction)","desc":"","updated":1650913893637,"created":1650913478417,"custom":{},"fname":"math.problems.tennis-defeated-induction","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"bdb1effdfb36eb33af9552e12463886d","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"math.problems.tennis-defeated-induction","id":"cxrxitu3f0mwbkymb3t367n","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"books.a-walk-through-combinatorics","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":7,"offset":6},"end":{"line":1,"column":45,"offset":44},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"books.a-walk-through-combinatorics"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"math.problems.tennis-defeated-induction","id":"cxrxitu3f0mwbkymb3t367n","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"math.induction","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1,"offset":46},"end":{"line":3,"column":19,"offset":64},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"math.induction"}}],"anchors":{"problem":{"type":"header","text":"Problem","value":"problem","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2},"solution":{"type":"header","text":"Solution","value":"solution","line":21,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"8sqzxw0w3t3uvomfp37adfr","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"tennis-defeated-induction\">Tennis Defeated (Induction)<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#tennis-defeated-induction\"></a></h1>\n<p>Book: <a href=\"/notes/67mq8dz09h7eycg8qe5waa8\">A Walk through Combinatorics</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"/notes/zzmafsnawboqura7kon24ih\">Induction</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"problem\">Problem<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#problem\"></a></h2>\n<p>At a tennis tournament, every two players played against\neach other exactly once. After all the games were over,\neach player listed the names of those he defeated, and\nthe names of those defeated by someone he defeated.</p>\n<p>Prove that at least one player listed the names of\neveryone else.</p>\n<h2 id=\"solution\">Solution<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#solution\"></a></h2>\n<p><strong>Base case</strong>, for 2 players, one player will write the other player's name.</p>\n<p><strong>Induction step:</strong></p>\n<p>For <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span> players, someone (say player <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span>) has written the name of all other players.</p>\n<p>Adding player <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n + 1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span>, player <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n + 1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span> has either won all games, then he has the list.</p>\n<p>Or player <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n + 1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span> has lost at least one game to one\nof the players <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span> to <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span></span>. Now since player <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span> has beaten all of these players, their list will get player <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n + 1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>So in any case, there is one player who has the list.</p>","noteIndex":{"id":